module:
   development.folder="dvlp">


    module, mathematics, value, atom, tuple 













     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record mathematical values. A
mathematical value can be used in the definition of a mathematical function or
maths space, or in the identification of a property value.





a maths value that is a real value;

a maths value that is an integer value;

a maths value that is a complex value;

a maths value that is a Boolean value;

a maths value that is a tuple of other maths values.






array and matrix values;


the association of units with a mathematical value.
The use of a mathematical value to identify a property
value with respect to a scale is within the scope of the
Property_identification application module.
